                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d294">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9673: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-26T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 26, 1937—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>177. The substance of your 498, August 23, 5 p.m., and 517 [<hi rend="italic"
                        >518</hi>], August 25, 10 a.m., has been repeated to Tokyo for communication
                    by the Ambassador to his interested colleagues.</p>
                <p>With regard to the question of possible action at Tokyo see Tokyo’s 313, August
                    25, 3 p.m. The Ambassador there has been informed that the Department is
                    inclined to concur with your view that it seems unnecessary to take up this
                    matter at Tokyo, but he has been authorized in his discretion to participate in
                    such action as may be considered desirable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
